The paper deals with deep neural networks (DNNs) and their generalisation, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper also uses information theory principles to derive an expression for the Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR) of a DNN node output, which is a topic in information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the qualities of weight sets that exhibit good SNR behaviour, which is related to network structure and optimisation, and hence could be categorised under cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
